  "text": "The xDS configuration discovery service flow follows a chain from the data plane API definition through the control plane Go implementation to the Envoy C++ client:\n\n**Protocol Definition (envoyproxy/data-plane-api):**\nThe `envoy/service/discovery/v3/ads.proto` file defines the `AggregatedDiscoveryService` gRPC service with two primary RPCs:\n- `StreamAggregatedResources(stream DiscoveryRequest) returns (stream DiscoveryResponse)` - State-of-the-world (SOTW) xDS\n- `DeltaAggregatedResources(stream DeltaDiscoveryRequest) returns (stream DeltaDiscoveryResponse)` - Delta xDS\n\nThe message types (`DiscoveryRequest`, `DiscoveryResponse`, `DeltaDiscoveryRequest`, `DeltaDiscoveryResponse`) are defined in `envoy/service/discovery/v3/discovery.proto`.\n\n**Go Control Plane (envoyproxy/go-control-plane):**\nThe protoc-gen-go-grpc compiler generates gRPC stubs in `envoy/service/discovery/v3/ads_grpc.pb.go` with the `AggregatedDiscoveryServiceServer` interface and handlers for `StreamAggregatedResources` and `DeltaAggregatedResources`. The Go bindings for `DiscoveryRequest` and `DiscoveryResponse` message types are in `envoy/service/discovery/v3/discovery.pb.go`.\n\n**Envoy Client (envoyproxy/envoy):**\nThe configuration subscription flow in Envoy implements a layered architecture:\n\n1. **Subscription Layer** (`source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_impl.h`): `GrpcSubscriptionImpl` provides a typed subscription adapter that wraps the untyped `GrpcMux` and handles per-xDS API stats and callbacks.\n\n2. **Mux Layer** (`envoy/config/grpc_mux.h`): The `GrpcMux` interface manages one or more gRPC subscriptions on a single stream to the management server. Two implementations exist:\n   - `GrpcMuxImpl` (`source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_impl.h`): Handles state-of-the-world (SOTW) xDS using `DiscoveryRequest`/`DiscoveryResponse`\n   - `NewGrpcMuxImpl` (`source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/new_grpc_mux_impl.h`): Handles Delta xDS using `DeltaDiscoveryRequest`/`DeltaDiscoveryResponse`\n\n3. **Stream Layer** (`source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_stream_interface.h`): The `GrpcStreamInterface` template defines the abstract interface for gRPC communication.\n\n4. **Stream Implementation** (`source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_stream.h`): The `GrpcStream` template class implements the actual bidirectional gRPC streaming using gRPC's `AsyncStreamCallbacks`. It:\n   - Establishes the gRPC channel using `establishNewStream()`\n   - Sends `DiscoveryRequest` or `DeltaDiscoveryRequest` messages via `sendMessage()`\n   - Receives responses in `onReceiveMessage()` and invokes `callbacks_->onDiscoveryResponse()` with the response\n   - Handles rate limiting and connection management\n\n5. **Delta State Management** (`source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/delta_subscription_state.h`): For Delta xDS, `DeltaSubscriptionState` maintains the protocol state, managing resource subscription interest and generating appropriate `DeltaDiscoveryRequest` messages in response to `DeltaDiscoveryResponse` messages.\n\n**Configuration Update Flow:**\nWhen an Envoy client needs configuration (e.g., clusters, routes, endpoints):\n1. A resource subscriber calls `GrpcSubscriptionImpl::start()` with resource names\n2. This calls `GrpcMux::addWatch()` to register interest\n3. The mux creates a `GrpcStream` that establishes a bidirectional gRPC stream to the control plane\n4. `GrpcStream::sendMessage()` sends a `DiscoveryRequest` (SOTW) or `DeltaDiscoveryRequest` (Delta)\n5. The control plane responds with `DiscoveryResponse` or `DeltaDiscoveryResponse`\n6. `GrpcStream::onReceiveMessage()` receives the response and calls `GrpcStreamCallbacks::onDiscoveryResponse()`\n7. The mux processes the response and invokes subscriber callbacks with the decoded resources\n8. Subscribers validate and apply the configuration\n\nThe v2 API variants are also supported via `envoy/service/discovery/v2/ads.proto` for backward compatibility."
}

